Knives Out was great! It was suspenseful, funny, heartwarming, a little dark, and just so much fun. It's the perfect movie to see with family during the Thanksgiving holiday.
Great movie.  The twist at the end was one of the best in a long time.  Lots of clues to lead you to the end.

Knifes out is the classic whodunnit murder mystery with a modern twist staring A-List actors such as Daniel Craig, Jamie Lee Curtis, Ana De Armas, and Chris Evans. Who bring the story to life captivating your attention with every twist and turn where with every revelation only brought forth more questions until the final scenes which tie the whole story together in the most unexpected and brilliant ways. 11/10 must see, one of the best movies of 2019.

Chock a film full of talented actors having a great time being mean or eccentric, add a clever plot peppered with plenty of cynical humor, and you get this delightful whodunit. The patriarch of a spoiled family (Christopher Plummer) is found dead on his 85th birthday and, of course, everyone has a motive. Enter a debonair Southern detective (Daniel Craig chewing up that accent) to solve the case. Chris Evans is especially enjoyable as the haughty, hateful grandson, while Toni Collette's new age entrepreneur is a hoot. (It's also a treat to see Frank Oz as the attorney.) The mystery keeps surprising right up til the end with lots of smart dialogue and stylish direction by Rian Johnson.
Hilarious I laughed throughout the whole movie!
Knives Out is an OK film....96% is way too high. More like 70% is accurate. Very good acting paired with a nice story. Very worthy way to spend 2 hours.

Seamless film that keeps moving at every turn, great characters and great fun to be had.  You will walk out satisfied, worthy of laying down your hard earned cash for the amount of fun you get in return!
